Create a visualization of a linear regression:

evals_day8 %>% ggplot(mapping=aes(x=age,y=score)) + geom_point() + geom_smooth(method="lm",se = FALSE)

Add the confidence interval:

evals_day8 %>% ggplot(mapping=aes(x=age,y=score)) + geom_point() + geom_smooth(method="lm",se = TRUE)

Create a linear model of score vs. age using a pipeline:

evals_day8 %>% lm(score ~ age, data = .) %>% get_regression_table()
## # A tibble: 2 x 7
##   term      estimate std_error statistic p_value lower_ci upper_ci
##   <chr>        <dbl>     <dbl>     <dbl>   <dbl>    <dbl>    <dbl>

## 2 age         -0.006     0.003     -2.31   0.021   -0.011   -0.001

data = . means whatever is mentioned on the left side that is here evals_day8.

Now let’s separate male and female:

ggplot(evals_day8, aes(x = age, y = score, color = gender)) +
  geom_point() +
  labs(x = "Age", y = "Teaching Score", color = "Gender") +
  geom_smooth(method="lm",se=FALSE)

And let’s create a linear model of score vs. age that takes gender into account:

score_model_interaction <- lm(score ~ age * gender, data = evals_day8)
# Get regression table:
get_regression_table(score_model_interaction)
## # A tibble: 4 x 7

Let’s take a look at a model that assumes there is no interaction:

gg_parallel_slopes(y = "score", num_x = "age", cat_x = "gender", 
                   data = evals_day8)

Let’s create a regression model that does not have an interaction term (note the formula uses ‘+’ instead of ’*’):

score_model_parallel_slopes <- lm(score ~ age + gender, data = evals_day8)
get_regression_table(score_model_parallel_slopes)

Learning Check 544.8.1:

Create a dataframe called “weather_day8” based on a random sample of 500 rows from weather that consists of only the following columns: temp (renamed from “Temperature (C)” ), apparent_temp (renamed from “Apparent Temperature ( C)”, humidity (from Humidity), and wind_speed (from “Wind Speed (km/h)”

weather_day8 <- weather %>% select(temp = `Temperature (C)`, apparent_temp = `Apparent Temperature (C)`, humidity = Humidity , wind_speed = `Wind Speed (km/h)`) %>% sample_n(500)

ggplot(weather_day8, mapping=aes(x=temp, y=apparent_temp)) + geom_point()

ggplot(weather_day8, mapping=aes(x=humidity, y=apparent_temp)) + geom_point()
